docs.abstract: Democrats painted the Supreme Court nominee as an archconservative who would endanger abortion rights and health care and protect President Trump.
docs.snippet: Democrats painted the Supreme Court nominee as an archconservative who would endanger abortion rights and health care and protect President Trump.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senate Democrats, facing an uphill struggle to defeat the nomination of Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh to the Supreme Court, opened a broad attack on Tuesday, painting him as an archconservative who would roll back abortion rights, undo health care protections, ease gun restrictions and protect President Trump against the threat of indictment.

headline.main: Senate Democrats Come Out Swinging in Long-Shot Fight to Block Kavanaugh
headline.print_headline: Fierce and Costly Fight Over Court Nomination Commences in Capitol

byline.original: By Sheryl Gay Stolberg, Mark Landler and Thomas Kaplan

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Justice Anthony M. headline.main: With Roe in the Balance, Two Republicans Hold High Court in Their Hands

docs.abstract: For the Kushner patriarch and his family, the pinnacle of American political power has turned out to be a wellspring of trouble, bringing criminal and regulatory inquiries.
docs.snippet: For the Kushner patriarch and his family, the pinnacle of American political power has turned out to be a wellspring of trouble, bringing criminal and regulatory inquiries.
docs.lead_paragraph: It was sweet redemption for Charles Kushner last year when his son Jared was named senior White House adviser. A dozen years earlier, a sordid scandal stemming partly from a family falling-out had reduced the senior Mr. Kushner from real estate baron to felon making wallets at a prison camp in Alabama.

headline.main: The Kushners Saw Redemption in the White House. It Was a Mirage.
headline.print_headline: Political Power Has Backfired For Kushners
